/graphics/charts_examples.html.description: These are some examples of how to use the charts in some real cases.

/graphics/colour_palette.html.description: This colour palette is only and exclusively to use in charts. Its use is only permitted when the primary colour palette is not enough.

/graphics/overview.html.description: This is a collection of data visualization standards created in order to give teams the library they need to quickly build full-fledged charting components.

/graphics/viz-rules.html.description: This checklist is meant to be used as a guide for the development of high impact data visualizations, describes what they do, as well as why and when they are most useful.

/guidelines/adopting.html.description: At LUCA, we want to create friendly experiences for our users. We define a simple attractive design, cool interactions at the source and then apply the solutions consistently across our product portfolio, trying to make sure people only have to learn them once. The LUCA Design System is plastic, flexible and allows for gradual adoption by our product teams. The UX Design team of LUCA Product Portfolio Department watches and control the adoption process across LUCA product portfolio progress across steps on each tool.

/guidelines/brand.html.description: Luca represents brand values, light, clarity of ideas, support to make the best decision, future and innovation. In everything we do, we aim to bring focus and clarity to teams without distracting; so our logo and symbol are direct, clear, and impactful. To accomplish this, we adhere to the guidelines below.

/guidelines/colour.html.description: Colour brings a design to life. It is used to express emotion and tone, as well as place emphasis and create associations. Colour should always be used in meaningful and intentional ways in order to create patterns and visual cues.

/guidelines/illustrations.html.description: Our visual language is clear and light regarding colour and concept. Light backgrounds and clear shapes are distinctive traits.

/guidelines/layout.html.description: Consider making layouts fluid and adaptive by default cause not every user will have their desktop browser maximized. This 12-column responsive grid provides the structure for websites and LUCA tools content, with flexible column widths and fixed gutters.

/guidelines/overview.html.description: LUCA Design System offers a common visual style that you can flexibly apply to a range of LUCA digital platforms. Our visual style offers a clean, modern aesthetic that meets high standards of visual accessibility while promoting credibility, trust, and warmth in the design.

/guidelines/typography.html.description: The text is the primary way that users understand and transmit content and identify our LUCA look and feel, so it’s important to use our corporate typographic principles, and -at the same time- to establish a clear visual hierarchy in order to maximize legibility.

/resources/downloads.html.description: These resources help you design LUCA products that match the LUCA design language. We provide multiple options for downloading the LUCA Design System, as well as specific downloads for icons, design tokens and swatches.

/resources/overview.html.description: These resources help you design LUCA products that match the LUCA design language. We provide multiple options for downloading the LUCA Design System, as well as specific downloads for icons, design tokens and swatches.

/uielements/accordion.html.description: Accordion enables users to expand and collapse sections of content.

/uielements/alerts.html.description: Notifications are messages that communicate information to the user.

/uielements/button_bar.html.description: Tabs organize and allow navigation between groups of content that are related and at the same level of hierarchy. Tabs can be nested into components like cards and sheets. Tabs control the UI region displayed below them.

/uielements/buttons.html.description: Buttons communicate the action that will occur when the user touches or click them.

/uielements/checkbox.html.description: Checkboxes are most commonly used to give users a way to make a range of selections (zero, one, or multiple).

/uielements/combobox.html.description: Combobox lets users choose one option from a list in a dropdown menu. It works well for lists of more than four choices when displaying them could clutter up the interface.

/uielements/info_navigation.html.description: This component allows to host the functions related to the charts present in the dashboards. Used to export to Excel, PDF, host the help tooltip and other related functions of the graph.

/uielements/list.html.description: Lists present multiple line items vertically as a single continuous element. Lists are best suited for similar data types.

/uielements/navigation_icons.html.description: Icons provide visual context and enhance usability.

/uielements/overview.html.description: Our system of UI components are designed to provide simplicity and consistency across all our services. These components provide a unified language and consistent look and feel when designing apps and products within the LUCA ecosystem.

/uielements/pagination.html.description: Pagination is used for splitting up content or data into several pages, with a control for navigating to the next or previous page. The default number displayed will vary depending on the context.

/uielements/pills_bar.html.description: Pills are compact elements that represent an input, attribute or action.

/uielements/popover.html.description: Popovers are small overlays that open on demand, usually when the user clicks a button. They let users access supplementary content and actions without cluttering the page.

/uielements/radio_buttons.html.description: Radio buttons allow users to see all available choices at once and select exactly one option.

/uielements/switch.html.description: Switches communicate an action a user can take. It is a control that is used to quickly switch between two possible states.

/uielements/tabs.html.description: Tabs organize and allow navigation between groups of content that are related and at the same level of hierarchy. Tabs can be nested into components like cards and sheets. Tabs control the UI region displayed below them.

/uielements/text_field.html.description: Text fields let users enter and edit text and usually appear in forms. Users may enter text, numbers, or mixed-format types of input.

/uielements/tooltips.html.description: A Tooltip is a small piece of contextual information about an element on the screen, which is displayed when a user hovers or focuses on the element it is describing or helping to understand, as an icon, a part of a chart or a piece of a module of a visualization.

/uielements/zoom.html.description: Group of buttons disposed in vertical position at the corner of a map or card. Their functions are maximize, minimize, drag and activate full screen.

/uielements.html.description: At LUCA we want to create great experiences for our tool’s users. Our design system helps us work together to build a great experience for all of LUCA’s designers and developers. We want to apply the desing and interaction in our tools and other solutions consistently across our product portfolio, making sure give to people an space for use and reuse with flexibility, continuosly revised and adapte to suit changing product needs.
